From 1111111111111111111111111111111111111111 Mon Sep 17 00:00:00 2001
From: henry <henry@example.com>
Date: Mon, 6 Jul 2026 17:12:00 +0800
Subject: [PATCH] pcie-rockchip-dma: avoid non-IRQ live mmio snapshots

0007 added UDMA/client/core register snapshots in DMA start, timeout,
IRQ, and debugfs paths. 0008 removed the debugfs live-MMIO read after
it was proven to hang the board in the current NPU/PCIe state.

The next real RKNN run on 0008 still made the board unreachable right
after the NPUTransfer client started. Avoid taking live MMIO snapshots
from the DMA work/timeout paths too; those paths run in the exact user
traffic path we are trying to keep alive. Keep cached register snapshots
only from IRQ handlers, where the controller has already signalled an
interrupt and previous evidence suggests the access is less risky.

This sacrifices some start/timeout register detail in exchange for not
turning diagnostic reads into another system hang trigger.
---
 drivers/pci/controller/pcie-rockchip-dma.c | 3 ---
 1 file changed, 3 deletions(-)

diff --git a/drivers/pci/controller/pcie-rockchip-dma.c b/drivers/pci/controller/pcie-rockchip-dma.c
--- a/drivers/pci/controller/pcie-rockchip-dma.c
+++ b/drivers/pci/controller/pcie-rockchip-dma.c
@@ -70,14 +70,12 @@
 	struct dma_table *tbl = obj->cur;
 	int chn = tbl->chn;
 
-	rk_pcie_dma_snapshot_regs(obj);
 	rockchip_pcie_write(rockchip, lower_32_bits(tbl->desc_dma),
 			    PCIE_APB_CORE_UDMA_BASE + 0x14 * chn + 0x04);
 	rockchip_pcie_write(rockchip, upper_32_bits(tbl->desc_dma),
 			    PCIE_APB_CORE_UDMA_BASE + 0x14 * chn + 0x08);
 	rockchip_pcie_write(rockchip, BIT(0) | (tbl->dir << 1),
 			    PCIE_APB_CORE_UDMA_BASE + 0x14 * chn + 0x00);
-	rk_pcie_dma_snapshot_regs(obj);
 }
 
 static void rk_pcie_prepare_dma(struct dma_trx_obj *obj,
@@ -201,7 +199,6 @@
 		return;
 
 	obj->dma_timeout_count++;
-	rk_pcie_dma_snapshot_regs(obj);
 	dev_warn_ratelimited(obj->dev,
 			     "pcie dma timeout: cur_type=%u loop=%d threshold=%d udma_status=0x%x udma_en=0x%x client=0x%x mask=0x%x core=0x%x core_mask=0x%x ctrl=0x%x desc=%08x:%08x list_empty=%d\n",
 			     obj->cur ? obj->cur->type : 0xffffffff,
